title: $750.00 Room For Rent (Castro Valley)
body_text:
b"Hello, I have a room for rent in lovely quiet Castro Valley near the CV Village Shopping Center: 
-12' X 9', 2nd Level, FURNISHED.  There are two pools, a small gym, and card-pay laundry, and parking is on-street. Your room is private, the bathroom, kitchen, and balcony are shared. The rest of the pad is my area. There's a nice couch in your room so you can set-up an entertainment center in there.
-Hi-Speed Wi-Fi, Water, Gas, Garbage, are ALL INCLUDED. Purchase cable TV if you wish. 
-2 blocks from BART, 2 blocks from Safeway, Lucky, Chevron, Starbucks, BofA, Wells Fargo, Chase,Walgreens, CVS, Chipolte, Mexican/Chinese/Italian/Thai/Sushi restaurants, and a Post Office. On-ramps to Highways 580/238 are about 2-minutes drive time.
-I am looking for one person (single occupancy only) and leaning toward a female (as that seems a better fit for me), 25 and up, perhaps a nursing student, a professional, or similar non-partying mature, CLEAN, and responsible adult, who will pay her rent on time. We will respect each other's space and be quite friendly and cordial, yet will not get into each other's business. 
-Zero Drugs, Zero Drama, Zero Drunks, Zero Pets, and a non-smoker is preferred (but if you smoke then on the balcony only not in the room or elsewhere inside okay).
-Typical rules apply (i.e. No overly loud music or TV, quiet times are 08:00am to 10:00pm (okay, 11:00pm on Fri/Sat), no cooking/smoking in the room, no Drama, and please love my two little doggies.
-Did I mention I have two little doggies?  Both are friendly and nice. (GET THIS: $25.00 off the monthly fee if you let them out to their balcony 'pee area' a few times a night while I am away or working! Otherwise they get crated which I and they don't like. That $25 off would include an occasional prearranged feeding on those rare times when I am away for extended hours, 1 or 2x a month).
-About me: I am a 55 year old professional male, respectful, clean, and easy to get along with, and not a jerk (usually).
-NOTE: Sorry but no guests. I've had nasty experiences with coming home to strangers roaming about, casing the place, drinking it up, leaving messes, and doing the 'Bim Bam' at 04:00am. Sorry, but no can do. (I'm flexible tho, so on the rare day your sister is in town from Alaska to visit, or an old friend calls then BY PRE-ARRANGEMENT ONLY we can make the rare occasional exception.) I simply do not want to come home to strangers in the pad. Again, sorry. 
PLEASE EMAIL ME WITH SOME INFO ABOUT YOURSELF AND WHY YOU THINK YOU WOULD MAKE A GOOD FIT. PLEASE NOTE, A CREDIT CHECK IS REQUIRED AS ARE REFERENCES (PARTICULARLY PRIOR LANDLORDS).
Thanks and good hunting!"

title: Webster Girls Shared Room - Monthly or Weekly - Downtown Palo Alto
body_text:
b"For more information please visit our website at www.rentashare.com

 
Welcome to our Hacker House that we originally started for Stanford Students and Affiliates. If you are a Stanford affiliate or an entrepreneur, or doing an internship in the valley then you might love this even more! (We have an all girls room here and the rest of the place is CO Ed) 

We provide the following: 

1. Linens and towels 
2. Utilities, and Wifi 
3. Cookware, Soaps, Shampoo, and Toilet Paper 
4. Bed in a bunk bed, with linens made 
5. Weekly maid service 
6. Laundry Machines 

So its pretty much everything you need for an easy transition into Downtown Palo Alto. Whether you're looking for longterm housing, or just want an easy clean place to work and lay your head with everything provided, we cater to people who need to be in Palo Alto, and are motivated towards succeeding in their endeavors. 

We do month to month and weekly bookings and prices are subject to change based on the availability. 

For updated information please visit our website at www.rentashare.com"

title: $1550 / 2br - 1100ft2 - Fully Furnished Bedroom w/ Private Bath in Oak
body_text:
b"Private room with private bathroom in West Oakland home.
Receives an amazing amount or natural light.
Fully furnished, with everything you need.

Comfortable queen bed with all linens and towels provided.
Access to kitchen and laundry machines.
Quick walk to 19th Street Bart Station, Lake Merritt, Uptown and Downtown Oakland
Easy access to Berkeley, Emeryville, San Francisco and South San Francisco.
Convenient for Kaiser, Highland Hospital, and Children's Hospital
Close proximity to San Francisco Ferry Terminal.
Plenty of street parking

$1,550 per month + half of the utilities

*Please include dates, something about yourself, your email address and phone number.
*No pets. I love animal but not in the house.
*Tours are available.
*No smoking"

title: Marina Bay Condo -- Gated Community
body_text:
b'I am looking to share my large 2 bed and 2 bath condo in Marina Bay. I am working professional who works at home and likes to relax over the weekend. The unit is setup to have one bedroom/bath on one side of the condo - the other on the opposite side so no shared walls which makes it "feel" bigger than it is.

About you:
Must be responsible, clean, and respectful.
No drugs and no smokers.
Pets - one already lives here.
Pay rent and bills on time 

a. A paragraph about who you are
b. $500.00 deposit + first and last month rent (before move in)
c. A Phone Number or Text Number and include the best time to reach you.
d. Personal References (3 if you can) or credit check

Month to month, but 3 month+ preferred. 

This can be available earlier if needed and we can pro-rate the rent.

The community includes 
gated parking, security on-site, state of the art gym, year round pool/hot tub, commuter shuttle to ferry, over night guest parkings

Your rent will include:
all utilities (gas/electric), monthly maid service, secure wireless high-speed internet + tv + access to streaming devices like Roku, your own bedroom and full bath with tub, kitchen with granite countertops, deck, fireplace in living room and some storage in outside closet. Covered Parking for $25.00 per month extra. Uncovered Parking is available within the gates.

Serious inquiries only. I will respond to everyone's questions/concerns in a timely manner.'
